<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF9CCE4CFCD5F8C7DFC33402" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF9CCE4CFCD5F8C7DECD3BEE" blockId="17.[810,1452,1814,2092]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF9CCE4CFCD5F8C7D8F73B1E" bold="true" box="[810,932,1814,1840]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF9CCE4CFBB4F8C7DFC03B1E" box="[1099,1171,1814,1840]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apalai">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF9CCE4CFBB4F8C7DFC03B1E" box="[1099,1171,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">apalai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the following combination of characters: Medium total length; PA pronounced, continuous to PI; two embolar keels, PAc absent; prolateral embolus without serrated area, represented by few (two–four) cusps distal to PAc.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF9CCE4CFCA0F81BDFC33402" blockId="17.[810,1452,1814,2092]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
